<h2>Setup Guide</h2>
<span>
  The goal of this guide is to ease the process of installing <%= company %> in your website.
  Please note that the guide is a work in progress and subject to change. We will reach
  out if any changes are required on your end after the setup is complete. 
</span>
<h3>1) Add <%= company %> DNS CNAME</h3>
<p>
  Please add this CNAME record to your websites DNS. This will enable traffic to be
  routed to <%= company %> though your domain name which will increase the defensibility
  of ads being delivered on your website. Feel free to <a href="mailto:<%= support_email %>">contact us</a> 
  if you don't know how, our team can walk you through it over the phone.
</p>
<div class="dns">
  <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
    <thead>
      <th><span>Record Type</span></th>
      <th><span>Name</span></th>
      <th><span>TTL</span></th>
      <th><span>Value</span></th>
    </thead>
    <body>
      <tr>
        <td>CNAME</td>
        <td><%= publisher.endpoint %></td>
        <td>300</td>
        <td><%= ads_domain %></td>
      </tr>
    </body>
  </table>
</div>
<h3>2) Select an Ad Network</h3>
<div class="networks">
  <div class="network left active" data-guide="carbon">
    <div class="image" style="background-image: url(/imgs/networks/carbon.png)"></div>
    <div class="name">Carbon</div>
  </div>
  <div class="network left" data-guide="dfp">
    <div class="image" style="background-image: url(/imgs/networks/dfp.png)"></div>
    <div class="name">Double Click</div>
  </div>
  <div class="network left disabled" data-guide="ad_sense">
    <div class="soon">coming soon</div>
    <div class="image" style="background-image: url(/imgs/networks/ad_sense.png)"></div>
    <div class="name">AdSense</div>
  </div>
  <div class="network left disabled" data-guide="rail">
    <div class="soon">coming soon</div>
    <div class="image" style="background-image: url(/imgs/networks/roll.png)"></div>
    <div class="name">AdRoll</div>
  </div>
</div>
<% include ./dfp %>
<% include ./carbon %>